SIMPLE: predispose
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predispose
<hw>Pre`dis*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Predisposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Predisposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pre-</ets> + <ets>dispose</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧disposer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To dispose or
incline beforehand; to give a predisposition or bias to; <as>as, to
<ex>predispose</ex> the mind to friendship</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make fit or susceptible beforehand; to give a
tendency to; <as>as, debility <ex>predisposes</ex> the body to
disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Predisposing causes</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<cd>causes which render the body liable to disease; predisponent
causes.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predisposition</ent>⟦br⟧
